==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonjuring
<hw>Non*ju"ring</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>jurer</ets> to swear, or L. <ets>jurare</ets>, <ets>jurari</ets>,
to swear, fr. L. <ets>jus</ets>, <ets>juris</ets>, right, law, justice.
See <er>Jury</er>.]</ety> <def>Not swearing allegiance; -- applied to
the party in Great Britain that would not swear allegiance to William
and Mary, or their successors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonjuror</ent>⟦br⟧
